===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|payle|t=wooden container}}, of {{unk|en|title=uncertain}} origin.

Possibly from {{inh|en|ang|pæġel|t=wine vessel, container for liquids, pail; liquid measure}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*pagilaz}}, equivalent to {{suffix|en|peg|le|nocat=1}}. Compare {{cog|dum|pegel|t=half-pint}}, {{cog|da|pægl|t=half-pint}}.

Alternatively from {{der|en|fro|paielle|t=pan, cooking vessel, liquid measure}}, from {{der|en|la|patella|t=shallow dish}}.

